Classes in sndlib.core.problem used by sndlib.core.problem
DemandFlow
          A DemandFlow is used to represent the flow between the source and the target node of a single demand in a network with respect to a specific solution.
DemandLinkFlow
          A DemandLinkFlow is used to represent the flow on a single link incurred by a certain demand w.r.t. a specific solution.
DemandPathFlow
          A DemandPathFlow represents the flow on a single path incurred by a certain demand w.r.t. a specific solution.
LinkFlow
          A LinkFlow is used to represent the flow on a single link in a network with respect to a specific solution.
OperatingState
          This class represents an operating state in a survivable network design instance.
OperatingState.Type
          Lists the admissible types of an operating state.
Problem
          A Problem couples a Network with a Model.
RoutingLink
          A RoutingLink is a component of a RoutingPath and wraps a single network link together with the direction of the corresponding flow.
RoutingPath
          This class represents a routing path in a specific solution of a network design problem.
RoutingPath.Builder
          This inner class abstracts the four static methods of RoutingPath.
